<docs>
   <doc for="UserControlDocumentDesigner">
 <summary>
    <para>Provides design-time functionality for user controls.</para>
 </summary>
   </doc>
   <doc for="UserControlDocumentDesigner.GetToolSupported">
 <summary>
    <para>Indicates whether the specified tool is supported by this 
       designer.</para>
 </summary>
 <param name='tool'>The tool that is to be enabled on the toolbox.</param>
 <returns>
 <para><see langword='true'/> if the tool can be enabled on 
    the toolbox; <see langword='false'/>
    if the document designer doesn't know how to use the tool.</para>
 </returns>
 <remarks>
    <para>If a tool is supported then it will be enabled in the toolbox when this 
       designer regains focus. Otherwise, it will be disabled. Once a tool is marked as
       enabled or disabled it may not be queried again.</para>
 </remarks>
   </doc>
   <doc for="UserControlDocumentDesigner.Initialize">
 <summary>
    <para>Initializes the designer with the specified component.</para>
 </summary>
 <param name='component'>The component to associate with this designer.</param>
 <remarks>
    <para>The designer can get the component's site and request services from it in 
       this call.</para>
 </remarks>
 <seealso cref='System.ComponentModel.Design.IDesigner'/>
   </doc>
   <doc for="UserControlDocumentDesigner.UserControlToolboxItem">
 <summary>
    <para> 
       Represents a toolbox item that is placed 
       on the toolbox for user controls.</para>
 </summary>
 <remarks>
    <para>This is identical to a standard toolbox item except that it displays a 
       special message when the class cannot be loaded.</para>
 </remarks>
   </doc>
</docs>

